{"lemma":"حَقِيبَةٌ","slug":"حَقِيبَةٌ","root":"ح.ق.ب","root_slug":"ح-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8596"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bag"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħa.qiː.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8596","headword_ar":"حَقِيبَةٌ","root":"Hqb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receptacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which a man puts his travelling-provisions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any other thing that is conveyed behind a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A [accord. to which this is a proper signification]:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the rider conveys behind him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF [accord. to whom this is a tropical significatiom, from the same word in the last of the senses mentioned below]:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is borne, of goods or utensils or the like, upon the horse, behind the rider:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb [accord. to which, also, this is tropical]:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is bound at the hinder part of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel's saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is put behind the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": they used to put the coats of mail behind their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riHaAl","text_ar":"رِحَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the [receptacles called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaAb","text_ar":"عِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", that they might put them on in case of war: (Ham p. 458:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro*aEap","text_ar":"بَرْذَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a covering for a camel's back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of two kinds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloth called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hilos","text_ar":"حِلْس"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is hollowed out, so as to admit the upper part of the camel's hump;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is behind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"ISh says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is placed upon the hinder part of the camel, beneath the two hinder curved pieces of wood of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifaAdap","text_ar":"رِفَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of pad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffed thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placed at the hinder part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqaAy^ibu","text_ar":"حَقَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaA^a Haqiybatahu","text_ar":"مَلَاَ حَقِيبَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hqybp","text_ar":"حقيبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arodafahu xalofahu EalaYAlHaqiybapi","text_ar":"اَرْدَفَهُ خَلْفَهُ عَلَىالحَقِيبَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to ride behind him on the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hqybp","text_ar":"حقيبة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an ideal kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that one takes upon himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lays up for the future"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be rewarded or punished for it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotamala Haqiybapa suwo'K","text_ar":"اِحْتَمَلَ حَقِيبَةَ سُوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took upon himself a burden of evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he bound it behind him: see 8]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albir~u xayoru HaqiybapK","text_ar":"البِرُّ خَيْرُ حَقِيبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Piety is the best thing that one can take upon himself, and lay up for the future"},{"kind":"text","text":"to profit thereby]. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also, accord. to the A, which I follow in marking this signification as tropical,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":611},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to the Msb and to MF it is the primary signification,] (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"posteriors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, MF, TA,) of a woman, (A, Msb,) and of a man: (TA:) pl. as above. (Msb.) So in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuju AlHaqiybapi","text_ar":"نُفُجُ الحَقِيبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the posteriors."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","TA","K","Msb","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}